Neighborhood Guides — Cafes, Coffee Shops & Restaurants (Rain-ready picks)
Notes: short reasons focus on covered seating, hot drinks, hearty bowls, decent indoor seating, and parking.

DTLA
- Grand Central Market (vendors: Eggslut, Ramen Hood, G&B Coffee) — communal covered seating and quick hot options.
- Perch LA (rooftop with covered seating options) — cozy cocktails and sweeping views when showers pause.
- Bottega Louie — pastries, warm drinks, and roomy indoor seating; good for made-for-rain days.
- Little Tokyo‑area ramen spots (e.g., Daikokuya) — steam bowls and covered sidewalks for minimal walk time.

Hollywood
- Musso & Frank Grill — old-school diner with covered entry and long indoor counter.
- G&B Coffee (Hollywood outpost) — excellent espresso, sheltered seating, and quick pastries.
- The Hungry Cat — seafood-forward with indoor seating and heated booths.

Koreatown
- Café Bora — cozy interiors and hot teas.
- Sun Nong Dan — hearty stews (galbi‑jjim) and indoor booths.
- The Perch (or similar covered cafés) — search for arcades and board game cafés with indoor seating.

Westwood
- Hammer Café (onsite at Hammer Museum) — warm drinks, sheltered seating.
- Coffee Bean & Tea Leaf (local cozy outposts) — quick and dependable stops with covered sidewalk access.
- Versailles Pastry & Café (Pasadena/Westwood nearby) — indoor pastries and warm drinks.

Miracle Mile / Mid‑Wilshire (incl. LACMA area)
- Ray’s & Stark Bar (LACMA) — views sheltered by large windows and hot meals.
- LACMA cafe — light meals and warming drinks.
- The Original Farmer’s Market (nearby) — indoor stalls and sheltered seating.

Pasadena
- Jones Coffee Roasters — small indoor seating, quality espresso, bikes parked inside.
- Cafe Santorini — warm interiors and parking nearby.
- Mi Piace (Old Pasadena) — warm pastas and indoor booths.

Live Weather Alerts & Notices (integrated)
- This post includes a small inline script that fetches weather alerts from OpenWeatherMap (or NWS fallback). Add OPENWEATHER_API_KEY to repository secrets to enable live alerts. When an active alert exists for the Los Angeles county area, a dismissible alert bar appears at the top of the post with alert summary and link to details. If alerts cannot be fetched, the bar links to the NWS Los Angeles office: https://www.weather.gov/lox/

Map placeholder — 'Hot soup index' layer
- The post contains a Mapbox/Leaflet container and a small JS placeholder where MAPBOX_ACCESS_TOKEN should be set. The map is a placeholder layer (hot soup index = simple choropleth by neighborhood). Add MAPBOX_ACCESS_TOKEN to enable map tiles.

Structured Data (JSON-LD)
- The page includes JSON-LD for Article, the five seeded Event items above, and LocalBusiness entries for recommended neighborhood cafés. This helps Ghost render rich snippets and improves search presentation.

ALERT BAR AND JSON-LD SCRIPTS (inline, runnable after secrets are configured)
- The file below includes inline JS that:
  - Fetches OpenWeatherMap one-call alerts for Los Angeles coordinates (34.0522, -118.2437) using OPENWEATHER_API_KEY.
  - Creates a dismissible alert bar at the top of the article when alerts exist.
  - Generates page JSON-LD for Article, seeded Events, and LocalBusiness entries.

Developer / Editor notes
- The JSON-LD events use startDate in ISO 8601 (with -08:00 PST offset). Confirm ticket URLs and times before final publish.
- The map and alerts are disabled if their API keys are not set (placeholders present).
- See scripts/fetch-events.js for a daily updater scaffold that can fetch live events and regenerate this page automatically.

